"{\"uid\": \"si.com-golf-stacked-leaderboard-sunday-final-round-olympics-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"SAINT QUENTIN-EN-YVELINES, France \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 The closing holes at Le Golf National hardly offer a feeling of serenity with a medal at stake on Sunday during the final round of the Olympic Golf Tournament.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 27, \"end\": 33, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9003670221409217, \"rank\": 0.07361483607597005, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jason Day got a taste of that during the third round Saturday and walked off the course ruing his missed opportunities.\", \"from\": 199, \"to\": 318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 199, \"end\": 208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Day\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.261199450039776e-97, \"text\": \"Jason Day\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Day\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Day\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian shot 67 which might have left him too far back in the chase for one of the top prizes with a stacked leaderboard that has Xander Schauffele and Jon Rahm on top.\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 319, \"end\": 333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5588707870279516e-13, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 456, \"end\": 473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xander Schauffele\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the fact that Day lamented that conclusion is what mattered.\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He cared far more than he ever dreamed.\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYes, by far, a lot more.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not only playing for your country and your teammates,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Day said.\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe crowd has made it fantastic to be a part of it.\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 752, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Definitely feel honored to be able to come here and represent my country.\", \"from\": 753, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been a fun week.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 848, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The dinners, team dinners have been tremendous and we had a lot of fun.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTypically we are always constantly trying to win tournaments on the PGA Tour.\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 993, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PGA_Tour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.385489360529765e-27, \"text\": \"PGA Tour\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PGA_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/PGA_Tour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We look at the money list and we look at what money we'd make.\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You do not earn anything this week.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are earning a medal, and I think that brings out something deep from whether it's when you are a junior golfer or amateur golfer that it means something more than just some money at the end of the day for us.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt's definitely opened my eyes, too; I have thoroughly enjoyed representing something bigger than myself.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's been a complete honor to do that.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  No matter how it ends on Sunday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and it has the potential to be really good\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the third version of the modern Olympic Golf has seen a transformation from indifference to acceptance to appreciation.\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE:A glance at the top contenders going into Sunday's final round  Day, 36, was the No.\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1-ranked player in the world when he skipped the Rio de Janeiro Games in 2016, golf\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first return in more than 100 years.\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1809, \"end\": 1823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.113006226953698e-19, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a blow to lose a player of his caliber, just as it was to not have Jordan Spieth and Dustin Johnson and Rory McIlroy and Adam Scott and others who were eligible.\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 2053, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Spieth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Spieth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Spieth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Spieth\"}, {\"begin\": 1977, \"end\": 1991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dustin_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dustin Johnson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dustin_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dustin_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 1996, \"end\": 2008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rory McIlroy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Zika Virus played a role in that but so, too, did a general malaise about golf and the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether it was the format, the crowded golf schedule, the relative unimportance of a gold or silver or bronze medal when the ultimate prizes in golf are green jackets or Claret Jugs, golf\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s return was less than spectacular.\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now it looks terrific, and a great leaderboard helps.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rahm, who won the Masters last year before leaving for LIV Golf last December, has found his form in recent weeks and shot 66 to tie two-time major winner Schauffele at 199, 14 under par.\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2493, \"end\": 2501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LIV_Golf\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LIV Golf\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LIV_Golf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LIV_Golf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Right behind is one of the second round co-leaders, Tommy Fleetwood, who shot 69 and is third, one stroke back.\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2679, \"end\": 2694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommy Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI am very, very excited to play,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Fleetwood said.\", \"from\": 2740, \"to\": 2794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2779, \"end\": 2788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9999763615416628, \"rank\": 2.363901270778785e-05, \"text\": \"Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou look at the leaderboard, the leaderboard is amazing.\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's like a leaderboard that you would expect at the Olympics and probably what the sport deserves, if you like.\", \"from\": 2855, \"to\": 2967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHappy to be a part of it and sort of been doing very well so far.\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 3037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So we will see.\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just looking forward to tomorrow.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Denmark\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Nicolai Hojgaard roared into contention with a course-record-tying 62 which is interesting for another reason\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094it tied the record also held by his twin brother, Rasmus.\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tied with 2021 Masters champion Hideki Matsuyama, just three back.\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3318, \"end\": 3334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hideki Matsuyama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Rory McIlroy (66) and Scottie Scheffler( 67) who are four shots behind.\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3369, \"end\": 3381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rory McIlroy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\"}, {\"begin\": 3391, \"end\": 3408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scottie Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Day is five back and tied for 10th\\u00c2\\u00a0with Ludvig Aberg.\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt's amazing for the game to see all those sorts of players up there,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d McIlroy said.\", \"from\": 3497, \"to\": 3586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cObviously Xander who has had an incredible year; Scottie, best player in the world; you have got Jon Rahm, some younger players; Nicolai shooting 62 today.\", \"from\": 3587, \"to\": 3745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3687, \"end\": 3695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Rahm\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jon Rahm\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Rahm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Rahm\"}, {\"begin\": 3719, \"end\": 3726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Nicholas\", \"score\": 0.9999970896430173, \"rank\": 2.910365117517077e-06, \"text\": \"Nicolai\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Nicholas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Nicholas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yeah, it's an amazing leaderboard and should be an exciting day tomorrow.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The day began with Schauffele, Fleetwood and Matsuyama tied for the lead and there was quite a bit of back-and-forth and moving around.\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3855, \"end\": 3864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9999763615416628, \"rank\": 2.363901270778785e-05, \"text\": \"Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 3869, \"end\": 3878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4955638391289415e-56, \"text\": \"Matsuyama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIlroy, who got himself back into the tournament with a front-side 33, said he couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009chelp myself\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d when it came to checking out the leaderboards.\", \"from\": 3961, \"to\": 4116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cDo not have the discipline not to,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said.\", \"from\": 4118, \"to\": 4167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was looking at it most of the round, especially when there is a couple of, like Tommy is up there and keeping an eye on how he's doing.\", \"from\": 4168, \"to\": 4308, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have been watching it a good bit.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  This is exactly what Olympic golf needed.\", \"from\": 4309, \"to\": 4390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A strong leaderboard with players who are stoked to win a medal is imperative.\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, so, too has been the venue.\", \"from\": 4471, \"to\": 4503, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Le Golf National, which hosted a very successful Ryder Cup in 2018, has been excellent, far better than expected as it relates to the fan experience and support.\", \"from\": 4504, \"to\": 4665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4504, \"end\": 4520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Golf National\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the course has been home to several big tournaments over the years, including the French Open, the country is not on the level of the United States and the United Kingdom when it comes to its golf passion.\", \"from\": 4666, \"to\": 4877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4806, \"end\": 4819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.5640519197574531, \"rank\": 0.7567822859353276, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4828, \"end\": 4842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999492320071, \"rank\": 2.6586926821668054e-08, \"text\": \"United Kingdom\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators have been out in full force, never more apparent when Frenchmen Viktor Perez or Matthieu Pavon do anything of note.\", \"from\": 4879, \"to\": 5005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4961, \"end\": 4966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CJ_Perez\", \"score\": 0.9999989510139176, \"rank\": 8.544626428097765e-07, \"text\": \"Perez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CJ_Perez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CJ_Perez\"}, {\"begin\": 4970, \"end\": 4984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthieu_Pavon\", \"score\": 0.9999999327346836, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthieu Pavon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthieu_Pavon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthieu_Pavon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And fans from other countries have found their way some 30 miles outside of Paris to fill the grandstands, concession lines and gallery ropes.\", \"from\": 5007, \"to\": 5149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5083, \"end\": 5088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999965348252, \"rank\": 3.4648477001528694e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI can not believe the amount of Irish support I have had out there,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Shane Lowry.\", \"from\": 5151, \"to\": 5242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5230, \"end\": 5241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shane_Lowry_(golfer)\", \"score\": 0.9805012734844502, \"rank\": 0.0198863636363513, \"text\": \"Shane Lowry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shane_Lowry_(golfer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shane_Lowry_(golfer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt's been incredible.\", \"from\": 5243, \"to\": 5267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I said to Darren (Reynolds, his caddie), not even doing well and they are still out there.\", \"from\": 5268, \"to\": 5358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's pretty cool.\", \"from\": 5359, \"to\": 5376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was in Tokyo (for the 2021 Olympics) as well, and let us be honest, it did not feel like a huge tournament but COVID, COVID was weird.\", \"from\": 5377, \"to\": 5513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5386, \"end\": 5391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998393336852427, \"rank\": 0.00016069213216317403, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut this certainly feels like one of the biggest tournaments in the world when you are here, which is pretty cool.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  McIlroy is one who changed his mind about the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5515, \"to\": 5692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now 35, he skipped in 2016, then contended for a bronze medal three years ago in Japan, losing in a seven-man playoff.\", \"from\": 5693, \"to\": 5811, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5774, \"end\": 5779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.8065365733830554, \"rank\": 0.2023257526236525, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterward, McIlroy said: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI never tried so hard to finish third.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s got a chance to do better than that on Sunday with a slew of people in contention.\", \"from\": 5813, \"to\": 5973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think the one thing that we have been taken aback by is just how many people are out there,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he said.\", \"from\": 5975, \"to\": 6083, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think that was the thing that I have been surprised by.\", \"from\": 6084, \"to\": 6144, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Especially the contrast of having no one here on the practice days, and then getting here and having 20,000 people, it's really cool.\", \"from\": 6145, \"to\": 6278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think that's been the big talking point, just how great the support has been for us out here.\", \"from\": 6279, \"to\": 6374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut yeah, I mean, I think I was in a certain mindset going into Tokyo and I left with a different mindset, just like I have done a lot of times in my career because I am ignorant and na\\u00c3\\u00afve and do not give things much thought.\", \"from\": 6376, \"to\": 6605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6443, \"end\": 6448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998393336852427, \"rank\": 0.00016069213216317403, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But once you experience things, you start to see what the hype is about.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Day has learned that as well as anyone.\", \"from\": 6606, \"to\": 6722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s admitted to making a mistake in skipping eight years ago.\", \"from\": 6723, \"to\": 6787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s no money (relatively speaking), no FedEx Cup points, no incentive, really, once you get beyond the top three medal spots.\", \"from\": 6789, \"to\": 6920, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Day said none of that matters.\", \"from\": 6922, \"to\": 6956, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics is different, pride is at stake.\", \"from\": 6957, \"to\": 7002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it was evident as he lamented bogeying two of his last five holes, making his task just that much tougher.\", \"from\": 7003, \"to\": 7113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt definitely feels like a major for sure, especially the crowd, standing on the first tee.\", \"from\": 7115, \"to\": 7209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I know the golf course is a tough one, and it would be really tough if we had stronger winds,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Day said.\", \"from\": 7210, \"to\": 7316, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think the way that they have prepared the golf course this week has been actually a lot of fun to play.\", \"from\": 7318, \"to\": 7426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it's been quite fair.\", \"from\": 7427, \"to\": 7456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think with history as it grows, I think this might turn into something of a major, the feeling of a major.\", \"from\": 7457, \"to\": 7565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt's really young, in its infancy.\", \"from\": 7567, \"to\": 7604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It just has to have some more history.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Sunday offers an excellent opportunity to build on that.\", \"from\": 7605, \"to\": 7704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 7706, \"to\": 7732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Bob Harig is a senior writer covering golf for Sports Illustrated.\", \"from\": 7733, \"to\": 7863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7797, \"end\": 7800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.5374891827429523, \"rank\": 0.46907334075000